The Deutsche Bahn is currently testing the ticket inspection system.
One simply confirms by mobile phone that one has taken his place and thus cancels the ticket.
There is currently a test run on two routes.
"When the offer arrives, we expand it.
It is expected to be available on many other long-distance routes in Germany at the beginning of next year, "said a railway spokesman.
"Comfort check" is what the train calls the ticket cancellation without a conductor.
However, in order to be able to use them, a few prerequisites must be met: You need a smartphone or a tablet.
And you have to have an online ticket booked - what already most passengers do.
You also have to buy it via the train app, the DB Navigator, which is the most convenient way to book tickets anyway.
Finally, you need a seat reservation.
Because the "comfort check" works like this: You get on the train, calls up your ticket under "My Tickets".
A button for electronic validation will then appear on the test customers.
The conductors are notified on their mobile devices that passenger X is on the train and has taken the booked seat Y.
If the conductor comes to seat Y at the ticket inspection, he knows that there is a passenger sitting there with an online ticket that has already been validated.
