Roll backwards: The city hires 46 kitchen helpers
The city organizes the day care center lunch itself again.
With fixed contact persons for the children and assignment to the team.
In the city ’ s day care centers, the clock is turned back.
As of September 1, the City of Krefeld will take over the food supply in the city ’ s day care centers (day care centers) on its own initiative.
For Sonja Pommeranz, deputy head of the Youth Services department, this is good news: "We were all very happy".
Cooking continues outside the house: a caterer takes on this task and delivers freshly cooked, chilled food.
The city runs 46 day care centers in the Krefeld area, in 44 children get a hot meal at noon.
Last year, 2800 children sat at the tables, and the demand is growing steadily.
